<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="450" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="450">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="450">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[322,531,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Clavidesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeri">
<emphasis box="[322,531,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="450">Clavidesmus egeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from its congeners by the distinct subcircular marking of dense, white pubescence on elytra. This species is described from a single female specimen collected at lights.
</paragraph>
